#~ "device, because you can split the storage up into chunks. The computer "
#~ "makes this storage accessible via your file system in a process referred "
#~ "to as <em>mounting</em>. Mounted volumes may be hard drives, USB drives, "
#~ "DVD-RWs, SD cards, and other media. If a volume is currently mounted, you "
#~ "can read (and possibly write) files on it."
